#  No other software installation needed
#  Expected run-time: ~ 2 minutes

# Instructions:
# 1. The script is located at Mutational-Signatures-JSD/JSD-Matlab/mut_sig_vs_conf_fingerprint.m
# 2. In the script choose which dataset to compare to mutational signatures (GT_Anion / AT_HG / GC_HG / AT_BaseOpening). The script will read the input file containing the conformational fingerprint (sequence contexts and rare state populations), and compute the Jenssen-Shannon-Divergence (JSD) with the cancer mutational signatures file (.txt file downloaded from the COSMIC database).
# 3. Output .csv files contain the full table of JSDs per substitution (transition mutation C>A, C>G, C>T, T>A, T>C, or T>G); as well as the best similarities between the SBS signature and the conformational fingerprint.
# 4. Another output file is a JSD table computed against a random distribution, for calculation of p-values and FDRs.
